==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fascicle
<hw>Fas"ci*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fasciculus</ets>, dim. of <ets>fascis</ets>. See
<er>Fasces</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small bundle or collection; a
compact cluster; <as>as, a <ex>fascicle</ex> of fibers; a
<ex>fascicle</ex> of flowers or roots</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the divisions of a book published in parts;
fasciculus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fascicled</ent>⟦br⟧
